208ff587-4592-41d4-9855-036f16827977.0fc8923d-0318-4b1c-bdca-a57d02b55e90.transition.description=Log files deleted from ${folder}. 208ff587-4592-41d4-9855-036f16827977.17e7c233-51dd-4f61-a2a4-84326b3b1c1c.description= Checks to see if a list contains every element in another list. inputs\: sublist - the contained list. container - The containing list. delimiter - A delimiter seperating elements in the two lists. responses\: success - sublist is contained in container. failure - sublist is not contained in container. 208ff587-4592-41d4-9855-036f16827977.1e28e75e-c090-4833-abca-1045792365c5.description= 
Checks to see if a path points to a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - the path to check
username - username to use when reading.
password - password to use when reading.

Responses\:
failure			- the operation failed. The path does not point to a directory.
success			- The operation succeeded.
208ff587-4592-41d4-9855-036f16827977.3f64dd5f-ec4f-46e6-aa0d-dd911ddce128.description= 
Compares a files last modified date/time to a given threshold.

Input Parameters\:
source - the file to read
Threshold - the threshold to compare the file modified time to.
username - username to use when reading.
password - password to use when reading.

Responses\:
failure			- the operation failed. The file probably could not be found.
greater than	- The file's modified time is larger than the threshold.
less than		- The file's modified time is smaller than the threshold.
equal to		- The file's modified time is the same as the threshold.

Extra Results\:
date			- The file's modified time.
208ff587-4592-41d4-9855-036f16827977.4612e7b9-a383-4504-8e41-8f0c7722e4f9.description= 
Gets a list of files and folders in a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - the directory to check
delimiter - A delimiter to put between files and folders in the directory.
username - username to use when reading.
password - password to use when reading.

returns\:
The children of the path.

Extra Results\:
count - the number of children.

Responses\:
failure			- the operation failed. The path probably could not be found, or was a file.
success			- The operation succeeded.

208ff587-4592-41d4-9855-036f16827977.b892621e-14d1-48a3-b16d-5b8273187ee0.description=Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - if the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - if some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.

208ff587-4592-41d4-9855-036f16827977.description=
moves or removes windows log files from a folder.

Inputs\:
alternateStore - Where to put log files. They are deleted if null.
folder - Folder to clean of windows log files.
user - user to authenticate as.
password - password for user.
Old Threshold - Files before this date will be cleaned.

Responses\:
success - operation completed.
failure - something went wrong.
flow.name: Clean Logs
